b'\xe2\x80\x9cGrowing up in Texas, #Juneteenth meant family gatherings, music and plenty of good barbecue to go around. It was a celebratory time. You see, as Black people we had to hold onto times of joy because outside, I felt the world was often saying: you\xe2\x80\x99re not good enough\xe2\x80\xa6you don\xe2\x80\x99t belong. But Juneteenth was, and is different. It was our day. It was an opportunity to put down the weight of the world and rejoice.\xe2\x80\x9d - David Huntley, SEVP & Chief Compliance Officer'
b'\xe2\x80\x9cJuneteenth has a special reminder this year that the struggle continues\xe2\x80\xa6freedom is not free.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x93 Victor @victorlankford'
b'\xe2\x80\x9cWe\xe2\x80\x99ll be wearing our crowns, highlighting our African culture and what we as a people have to celebrate.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x93 Victor @victorlankford'
b'#Juneteenth is a special day that holds a new significance this year. Keysha shares how she\xe2\x80\x99s celebrating and the meaningfulness of this day.'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cWhat will you do when the conversation is over?\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x93 Keathen @swyfoundation'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cOn this journey to eradicate racial injustice, let\xe2\x80\x99s make sure that our actions are not only a mere rest stop along the way, but rather a landmark for change. It\xe2\x80\x99s almost summer and I\xe2\x80\x99m sure everyone\xe2\x80\x99s ready to get back into golfing shape! As an #ATTAthlete, it\xe2\x80\x99s been amazing to see @ATT supporting virtual learning businesses in the wake of #COVID19. In the spirit of that initiative, sharing a few of the ways I\xe2\x80\x99ve been warming-up at home:

1. Stretch! If don\xe2\x80\x99t have weights to stay activated and mobile, use a foam roller, stretching activations, or any kind of resistance bands and a mat.\xc2\xa0
2. Focus on putting, working on stroke path and start-line. At home I use poker chips as barriers, and the ball has to start through the last two sets of poker chips.\xc2\xa0
3. Lastly, remember ball position and alignment. I use an alignment stick to align feet at target but also pointed for ball position. 
Don\xe2\x80\x99t overthink it\xe2\x80\xa6 just focus on getting back to basics! 
#ConnectedTogether'
